# React Frontend Conventions

## Project Structure

```
pulse-ui/src/
├── screens/        # Page-level screens (one folder per route)
├── components/     # Shared reusable components
├── hooks/          # Custom React hooks (API/data)
├── stores/         # Zustand stores (client state)
├── constants/      # App constants, routes, API routes, OTEL semconv
├── helpers/        # Auth, cookies, API helpers (makeRequest)
├── types/          # Shared TypeScript types
├── utils/          # Utility functions
├── clients/        # API client setup
├── mocks/          # MSW mocks
└── theme/          # Mantine theme configuration
```

## Screen Folder Structure

Every screen in `screens/<ScreenName>/`:

```
ScreenName/
├── index.ts                 # Barrel export
├── ScreenName.tsx           # Main component
├── ScreenName.module.css    # Scoped styles
├── ScreenName.interface.ts  # Props and types (optional)
├── ScreenName.constants.ts  # Strings, options, configs (optional)
└── components/              # Sub-components (same pattern)
```

Complex screens may also contain:
- `hooks/` — screen-specific hooks
- `utils/` or `helpers/` — screen-specific utilities
- `constants/` — subfolder for multiple constant files
- `pages/` — sub-pages within a screen

## Shared Component Pattern

Each component in `components/<ComponentName>/`:

```
ComponentName/
├── index.ts                    # Barrel export
├── ComponentName.tsx           # Component implementation
├── ComponentName.module.css    # Scoped styles
├── ComponentName.interface.ts  # Props types (optional)
└── ComponentName.constants.ts  # Constants (optional)
```

Nested component groups (e.g., `Charts/`) can contain sub-component folders following the same pattern.

## Custom Hook Pattern

Each hook in `hooks/<useHookName>/`:

```
useHookName/
├── index.ts                    # Barrel re-export
├── useHookName.ts              # Hook implementation
└── useHookName.interface.ts    # Types for params/response
```

Related hooks may be grouped in one folder (e.g., `useSdkConfig/` contains `useGetActiveSdkConfig.ts`, `useCreateSdkConfig.ts`, etc. with a shared `useSdkConfig.interface.ts`).

## File Naming

| Type | Convention | Examples |
|------|------------|---------|
| Screens | PascalCase folder + `.tsx` | `UserEngagement/UserEngagement.tsx` |
| Components | PascalCase folder + `.tsx` | `PageHeader/PageHeader.tsx` |
| Hooks | `use*` camelCase | `useGetInteractionDetails.ts` |
| Interfaces | `*.interface.ts` | `UserEngagement.interface.ts` |
| Constants | `*.constants.ts` | `AppVitals.constants.ts` |
| Styles | `*.module.css` | `UserEngagement.module.css` |
| Barrel exports | `index.ts` (or `index.tsx` for route definitions) | `screens/index.tsx` |
| Props types | `<ComponentName>Props` | `UserEngagementProps`, `LineChartProps` |

## Constants Organization

```
constants/
├── index.ts                # Barrel exports
├── Constants.ts            # API_ROUTES and ROUTES objects
├── Constants.interface.ts  # Route type definitions
└── PulseOtelSemcov.ts      # PulseType, STATUS_CODE, COLUMN_NAME enums
```

## UI Framework

- **Mantine v7** for all components (`AppShell`, `Button`, `Modal`, `Select`, etc.)
- **Tabler icons**: `@tabler/icons-react`
- **Charts**: `echarts-for-react` (wrapped in `components/Charts/`)
- **Data tables**: `mantine-datatable`

## State Management

- **Server state**: TanStack Query v5 (`useQuery`, `useMutation`)
- **Client state**: Zustand with `devtools` middleware
- **Forms**: `react-hook-form`

## API Integration

- Use `makeRequest<T>()` from `helpers/makeRequest/` — handles 401 refresh automatically
- API routes in `constants/Constants.ts` → `API_ROUTES`
- Base URL: `REACT_APP_PULSE_SERVER_URL`
- Custom hooks in `hooks/` wrap `useQuery`/`useMutation` + `makeRequest`

## Routing

- React Router v6 — routes defined in `Constants.ts` as `ROUTES`
- Screen barrel exports in `screens/index.tsx`
- Add new routes to both `ROUTES` object and `App.tsx` `<Route>` tree

## Styling

- Prefer CSS modules: `import classes from "./Name.module.css"`
- Use Mantine CSS variables: `var(--mantine-spacing-md)`, `var(--mantine-color-gray-6)`
- Layout with flexbox/grid
- Inline `style={{}}` is acceptable for dynamic or one-off styles

## Types

- Export interfaces in `*.interface.ts` files co-located with components
- Props type naming: `<ComponentName>Props`
- Shared types in `types/` directory
